text: Rosanne Cash (born May 24, 1955 ) is an American singer, songwriter and author. She originally did country music, but then expanded to pop, folk and rock music. Cash has had many hit songs during her singing career. She is the daughter of Johnny Cash. Rosanne Cash was born in Memphis, Tennessee. She moved to Nashville in 1981, and New York City almost nine years later. ==References== Category:American singer-songwriters Category:singers from Memphis, Tennessee Category:1955 births Category:Living people Category:American writers Category:American country singers Category:American pop singers Category:American rock singers
